@node "Contents" "DazWall - Archive Contents"

                                @{b}Contents@{ub}

When you extract the DazWall-archive, the following files *MUST* be there:

                                   ­­­­

daydream/doors/DazWall/Dazwall.dd    - The wall itself. You can't use Daz-
                                       Wall if you don't have this file.

daydream/doors/DazWall/DazWall.guide - The guide you're staring at right
                                       now.

libs/rexxsupport.library             - I used this library for some
                                       non-standard arexx-commands. Put
                                       this in your LIBS: directory or
                                       Dazwall won't run.

libs/rexxsyslib.library              - It's the standard arexx-library
                                       you'll need for EVERY arexx-script,
                                       so I included it, although you'll
                                       probably have it already.

c/sort                               - You'll probably already have this
                                       utility in your c: directory, but
                                       DazWall needs it, so I supplied it.
                                       Just in case...

                                   ­­­­

After running the door once, the following 3 files will be created:

doors:dazwall/DazWall.cfg            - The default configfile.
doors:dazwall/Wall.data              - the datafile where all the tags
                                       and the statistics are kept.
doors:dazwall/User.log               - The datafile that is needed to
                                       create the Top-10-List.

                                   ­­­­

You can make an @{b}optional@{ub} file, called 'Banned.cfg' in the doors:dazwall-
directory. This file is used to @{"Ban" link "banning" 0} users.

Another @{b}optional@{ub} file, called 'Wordban.cfg' can be put in the same
directory to avoid certain words to appear on the wall. (see @{"Word-Ban" link "WordBan"}

                             @{" Back to Main " link "Main" 0}

@endnode

@node "Important" "DazWall - Things You Should Know"

                               @{b}Important@{ub}

The DazWall.rexx @{b}may not@{ub} be changed in @{b}any@{ub} way! I know
it's very easy to de-optimize the script and change whatever you want,
everybody could do that. I suggest you leave DazWall.rexx the way it
is. If you want any new features or find some bugs, you can @{"Contact" link "contact" 0} me.
Besides, if you change anything in the wall, there's a big chance that
DazWall doesn't work anymore.

                             @{" Back to Main " link "Main" 0}

@endnode

@node "WordBan" "DazWall - Word-Ban"

                               @{b}Word-Ban@{ub}

It is possible to prevent users to use certain words you rather not want
to see on @{b}DazWall@{ub}. That's why I implanted a @{b}Word-Ban@{ub}
option. To use this feature, just create a file called Wordban.cfg and put
it in the doors:dazwall/-directory. In this file you put the words you want
to ban from the wall, each word on a new line.

                 The Word-ban feature is case sensitive!!

                             @{" Back to Main " link "Main" 0}
@endnode

@node "History" "DazWall - History"

                                @{b}History@{ub}

@{b}1.00@{ub}  : - First attempt of a Wall for Daydream.
        - Very simple.
        - Very ugly design.
@{b}1.01@{ub}  : - Port to /X of v1.00.
        - New design by HiFi, better, but still ugly.
@{b}...@{ub}     - More options.
        - Better code.
@{b}2.x@{ub}   : - Online configuration program added.
@{b}3.0ß1@{ub} : - Dazzler started developping again.
        - Complete New Design by Radavi.
@{b}3.0ß2@{ub} : - Port to /X by HiFi.
        - Cleaned up the code (big time!).
        - Faster.
        - Smaller.
        - If 's:dazzled-wall.cfg' and.
          'doors:eft-doors/dazzled-wall/Wall.data' aren't found, default-
          files are automaticly made instead of asking for it. This will
          happen without any notification.
@{b}3.0ß3@{ub} : - Added cursor-support on colour-selection.
        - Fixed some small 'bugs' in the code.
        - Fixed the infoscreen.
@{b}3.0ß4@{ub} : - Removed online configger.
        - Removed some bugs again.
        - Optimized code a bit.
        - New information-screen.
        - Started coding a new online configger.
@{b}3.0ß5@{ub} : - Online Configger with cursorsupport finished.
        - Removed the 'sysop-tagcolour' configuration option.
        - New path/name (doors:eft-doors/dazzled-wall/dazzled-wall.rexx ->
          doors:dazwall/dazwall.rexx).
        - New name for configfile (s:dazzled-wall.cfg -> s:dazwall.cfg).
        - 'Intelligent' config-saver added.
          · If the config is changed, the configger will ask you to
            save the changes or not on exit. If no changes are made, the
            configger will quit quietly.
        - Updated the 'info'-screen a bit, now with boardnumbers.
@{b}3.0ß6@{ub} : - Major optimizing in online configger, maximum speed on
          cursormovement in lists now. (thanks Radavi to kinda give
          me the 'hint', although he didn't realise it :).
          · List-updating only redraws 2 lines now instead of 3.
          · Far more efficient possition-checking.
          · Much smaller code.
          · Much faster.
        - Cursor-position for remote users fixed. Cursor in configger
          now ALWAYS on [25;79H (not in the middle of the screen anymore)
          Local users will see no cursor when it's not needed.
        - More cleaning done in the code.
        - Rexxopt Size now: 11762 bytes!.
@{b}3.0ß7@{ub} : - Fixed bug that caused the door to jam if the user entered the.
          configger and went straight to the colour/white and pressed
          enter without using the cursorkeys. I forgot to define the
          'oldpos' variable.
        - Added configfunction 'Minimum Access Level' to the configger.
        - If the wall is cleared, it will be shown immediately.
        - Bug removed that caused the door to quit when the user pressed
          a key while showing information-screen.
        - Fixed a tiny little bug concerning the question "Want to save
          the changes you made?" when you want to exit the configger.
          · Changed default answer from 'N' to 'Y'.
        - Fixed some cursor-problems on local users.
@{b}3.0ß8@{ub} : - Removed an superfluous line in the source (very small fix).
        - Changed the word 'Dazzled-Wall' at the end to 'DazWall'.
        - Started coding on the 'statistics'-part.
        - The number of named- and anonymous-tags are being tracked and
          stored in 'Top.data'. You can now view the (still limited)
          statistics by pressing 'S' at the main prompt of the wall
        - Changed the Version-string in the Information-screen.
@{b}3.0ß9@{ub} : - Big update! Read the below carefully!
        - *MOVED* the s:DazWall.cfg to Doors:DazWall/DazWall.cfg.
          The path to the door CAN NOT be changed anymore, it MUST be
          doors:dazwall/.
        - Removed the first line in DazWall.cfg (path) because it wasn't
          necessary anymore.
          · Remove this line by hand or copy the supplied DazWall.cfg to
            doors:DazWall/DazWall.cfg.
        - Removed doors:dazwall/Top.Data and implanted that data in
          doors:dazwall/Wall.data, just add the 2 lines in Top.data to
          the Wall.data (at the bottom) and delete Top.data.
        - Added an OPTIONAL slotnumber-ban. If you don't want certain
          users to tag on the wall, make a file called 'Banned.cfg' in the
          doors:dazwall-dir. The first line of this file contains the number
          of users that are banned from the users and the lines 2 to <x>
          contain the SLOTNUMBERS (*NOT USERNAMES!*) to ban from the wall.
          If banned.cfg isn't found, dazwall asumes that there are NO banned
          users.
          · I used *SLOTNUMBERS* instead of usernames because it's far more
            effective. If I used usernames, a banned user could simply
            regain access to the wall by changing his name.
          · Banned users can do everything EXCEPT for tagging on the wall.
            They can still view the stats or change the config (if they
            have the right accesslevel for it).
        - I Rewrote the statistics-file-handling. Should be somewhat faster
          now.
        - Changed the default doors:dazwall/dazwall.cfg a bit.
        - Changed the info-screen again.
@{b}3.0ß10@{ub}  - Some sort of EMERGENCY update! - better not use ß9 !!
        - I fucked up MAJOR on the configfile.
          · Some configline were still expected to be somewhere else.
          · Strings configuration was fucking up big time.
          · Clear Wall fucked up with the statistics.
        - The statistics are NOT cleared when the wall is.
        - Fixed a bug concerning the strings-configuration.
          · When you changed a string, the wall didn't ask if you want
            to save the config before exiting.
        - Nothing new, just bugfixing ß9.
@{b}3.0ß11@{ub}  - When you clear the wall, the statistics will be set to 0 too.
        - Big addition to the Statistics!
          · Every time a user enters a named tag, his handle will be
            added to doors:dazwall/user.log.
          · This logfile is used to create a Top-5-list in the statistics-
            screen with the 5 users who made the most tags to the wall.
            For now, the routine is limited to a logfile with no more than
            9999999 entries, which must be enough for normal use :)
            (It will take ages anyway to calculate 9999999 entries anyway).
          · The calculation-routines are not very fast, but that's because
            I had to use some dos-commands (c:sort for example) to create
            the top-5-list. It was a bitch to programm in Arexx but I'm
            very content with the result. Needs some Beta-Testing though
        - When the wall is cleared, user.log will be cleared too.
        - Already fixed a bug in the Top-5-Taggers, looks better now.
        - Better user.log handling, if user.log doesn't exists, no
          top-5-list will be created.
          · *DO NOT* make a 0 byte user.log! (The statistics will crash)
            Just delete the file, or use the Clear-Wall function.
        - Anonymous tags will not be added to the user.log due to
          'privacy' reasons. I don't want to create a 'big brother is
          watching you'-effect.
        - Little tip: if you don't want to ban any users, it's better to
          DELETE doors:dazwall/Banned.cfg rather than inserting a zero at
          the top. (it saves some speed...)
        - You now need Rexxsupport.library (everybody has it I think?)
          because I used the internal 'delete'-function rather than calling
          c:delete (for better compatibility and speed).
        - Used the Rexxsupport.library-function DELAY() instead of c:wait
          for the same reasons as above.
@{b}3.0ß12@{ub}  - Optimized the box-drawing-routine, the box is now drawn much
          faster.
        - Optimized a little bit in the code to gain speed (not noticable
          though, but I want to keep the source as small as possible)
        - From now on only the files 'DazWall.rexx' and 'Update.txt' will
          be in the release-LHA-archive because all other files will be
          created automaticly when you start the door for the first time.
        - Changed the Censure-routine a bit. It's somewhat smaller now.
        - Fixed a little bug concerning the number of anonymous/named tags.
          · The door crashed when the data was about to be saved and
            NrAno or NrNam weren't defined.
        - Changed the Top-5-List a bit to allow longer usernames.
        - Fixed a bug in the Top-5-List.
          · When the username was more than 16 chars, the display fucked up.
            The username is now cut after 16 chars.
        - Moved the Getuser for SlotNumber. Now it's only retrieved when
          doors:Dazwall/Banned.cfg exists. Should make the door a split-
          second faster :)
        - Removed some unnecessary defines (white="[37m"+more) at the
          beginning of the door to speed things up a little (the door should
          start faster now)
        - Fixed some VERY small and harmless bugs concerning the display,
          hardly noticable though.
@{b}3.0ß13@{ub}  - Fixed a small display-bug concerning the configger, nothing
          serious, just looked weird.
        - Another small pure cosmetical fix.
        - I added support for 1-bitplane-screen-users.
          · If you only use 2 colours in your terminal you practicly
            couldn't use the online-configger and the censure-option,
            because they fully work with colours. So I added some <'s to
            it. They are not visible in multicolour-environments, but they
            are of great help in 1bpl-mode. Thanks to Interphase to give
            me a note of this.
        - Fixed a bug in the Check-Ban-Routine.
          · The 'Sorry, You Are Banned'-line as only showed once, so the
            'banned' user could still tag on the wall at the second atempt.
        - Fixed a little bug in the Default-CR-configuration.
          · The configger didn't ask to save the config when the user changed
            the deafult answer on a 'CR'
        - Added a new statistics-thingy.
          · Now the number of removed lines will be shown in the statistics-
            window.
        - Updated the Number Of Removed Lines routine.
          · Now, when a line is removed, it'll be deducted from the NrAno or
            NrNam-variables (depending on the state of the removed line
            (ANONYMOUS/NAMED)).
        - Fixed a BIG bug in the Top-5-List.
          · It's too hard to explain, but it just didn't work well. I
            *HAD* to make a very slow routine. Maybe I can speed it up
            later. I hope it works ok now.
        - Removed a bug in the SaveData.
          · I accidentally used a READ-command while I had to use a
            WRITE-command.
        - Removed a bug which caused the wall to jam if the user entered
          the Remove-A-Line-function, and removed the first line (without
          using the cursorkeys). The oldpos-variable wasn't defined yet so
          the wall jammed. Fixed now.
        - Fixed a bug in the Tags-Counter.
          · It added 1 to Nr.Removed and deducted 1 from Nr.Named if a
            user removed a) An already removed line, b) an empty line, or
            c) the Dateline. This is all fixed now. Removing empty/censured/
            date-lines will have no effect on the counters.
@{b}3.0ß14@{ub}  - Fixed a very important bug in the Top-5-List (sigh .. again ..)
          · When a user has more than 10 tag-entries, he will most likely
            end up on the wrong place in the list, that's fixed now (thank
            God 'c:sort' has a NUMERIC option ... :)
        - Enhanced the Colour-Configuration a bit.
          · The selector will now appear at the CURRENT colour, not on the
            default 'white'.
        - Enhanced black/white user-support.
          · When you select a border-colour in the configger, you will see
            the colour in the status-line so you don't have to guess what
            colour you selected last.
        - Enhanced the 'Changed'-routine.
          · Now, the configger only asks to save the config (on exit) when
            the current colour is different from the one in the config. If
            it's still the same, it won't be asked.
        - Made some small fixes in the display of the configger.
          · There were still some small bugs concerning a small vertical
            blue line, this is all fixed now.
        - Removed *LOTS* of unnecessary cursor-placement-codes which made
          the display smaller and faster.
        - Made a big speed-improvement on the 'scrolling lines 1 char up'-
          routine which is used when a user wants to tag on the wall.
        - Removed some stupid routines that where only there to slow down
          the wall. Result: more speed.
        - Made a beginning on the Amigaguide-documentation.
        - Implanted the Update.txt in DazWall.guide.
        - Fixed a little bug that sneaked into 3.0b13.
          · The screen was cleared first when the user selected another
            bordercolour. This is fixed now.
        - By removing one single line in the source, I managed to *DOUBLE*
          the speed of the 'One Char Up'-routine when a user decided to tag
          on the wall! Big speed increase!
        - From now on, the sysop CAN NOT be banned. If the slotnumber appears
          to be '1', the ban-option is de-activated (this only occurs when
          there's been set a ban on slotnumber '1' (=sysop))
        - The user with slotnumer 1 (sysop) can ALWAYS enter the online
          configuration program, no matter what's his accesslevel.
        - Cleaned up the code a bit again. Made some slighty speed-
          improvements and the code somewhat smaller again.
        - Changed the Top-5-list to a Top-10-List. Interphase thought that
          5 users in the list wasn't enough.
        - Fixed a bug in the colour-selection
          · the '<' wasn't shown on the right place most of the time.
        - The Number-1-Tagger in the Top-10-List is now shown in BOLD.
        - Added some sort of 'what is it doing'-statusline to the Top-10-
          list, because it could take a while for the door to calculate the
          top-10-list. So it's less boring :)
        - This is probably gonna be the FINAL VERSION.
@{b}3.0ß15@{ub}  - Fixed a few tiny things concerning the cursor-placement.
        - Finished the DazWall.guide.
        - I don't know how it happened, but I had to fix *another* bug in
          the statistics-window.
          · When you removed an Anonymous tag with the configger, there was
            also 1 deducted from the Named Tags. This is fixed now.
        - Discovered a small bug in the Top-10-List.
          · When several users have made the same amount of tags on the wall,
            their names aren't shown in alphabetical order, this is because
            I had to use the 'numeric'-parameter in 'sort'. This can't be
            fixed without rewriting the whole Top-10-List-routine.
        - Added cursor-support to the first question.
          · You can now move the cursor to the following:
            "Yes"    "No"   "Config"   "Stats"   "Info" and press enter to
            activate it. Now it's more clear to the user which options there
            are in DazWall. The Y/N/C/S/?-keys are still valid though.
        - Added a Wordban option (on request of interphase)
          · You can now put a file named 'wordban.cfg' in doors:dazwall/
            which contains the words you don't want to be used on the
            wall. The checker is case-sensitive and can't be used on
            sentences.
@{b}3.0ß16@{ub}  - Found and fixed some problems on multinode-systems.
          · If more users are using Dazwall at the same time on different
            nodes, problems could occur when a datafile was accessed twice
            at the same time. Because this is not likely to occur very
            often, I decided to let the second wall wait for the first to
            finish before proceding, the user will get a notice of this.
	- First release!

                             @{" Back to Main " link "Main" 0}

@endnode
